discrimination based on sexual orientation. He also examines less prominent, but equally compelling cases, including McCleskey v. Kemp, which involved statistical evidence that a state’s death penalty was disproportionately used when victims were white and defendants were black, and Castaneda v. Partida, which established key standards of evidence in addressing the exclusion of Latinos from grand jury service. For each case, Ancheta explores the tensions between scientific findings and constitutional values.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aDiscriminationxLaw and legislationxUnited States. 0aDiscriminationxLaw and legislationzUnited States. 0aDiscriminationxResearchxUnited States. 0aDiscriminationxResearchzUnited States. 0aEquality before the lawxResearchxUnited States. 0aEquality before the lawxResearchzUnited States. 0aEquality before the lawxUnited States. 0aEquality before the lawzUnited States. 0aScience and lawxUnited States. 0aScience and law. 7aLAW / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertRutgers University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311068861040uhttps://doi.org/10.36019/978081353931740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780813539317423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780813539317.jpg  a978-3-11-068861-0  Rutgers University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LAEC  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LAEC  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA18STMEE  aPDA5EBK